The paper discusses a technique for designing beamforming vectors in a massive MIMO system, which involves computational complexity and statistical robustness. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on signal processing and optimization techniques, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are less likely but still possible, as they may involve similar techniques or applications.
